The People’s Democratic Party (PDP), has congratulated the Olu of Warri, His Royal Majesty, Ogiame Atuwatse II, Tsola Emilio, on his ascendancy to the throne as the 21st Olu of Warri.  The party gave the congratulatory message in a statement issued by its National Publicity Secretary, Mr Kola Ologbondiyan in Abuja on Tuesday. According to the party, the new Olu of Warri has been divinely ordained and exceptionally gifted, equipped and endowed with youthful energy, wisdom, insight and capacity for the task ahead of him. The party urged the new traditional ruler to deploy his exalted position in further uniting his people. It also urged him to provide the desired leadership that could guarantee stability and higher productivity for the benefit of his people and the nation at large. The party expressed happiness over the emergence of a youthful Olu of Warri. “The development is in line with the party’s desire and commitment to have more youths in leadership positions.’’ The party urged the traditional ruler to use his wealth of experience and exposure for the good of the people. It also congratulated the people of Warri as well as the government and people of Delta State. The party prayed to God to continue to shower the new Olu of Warri with good health and more wisdom to lead his people.